&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Armis, &lt;strong&gt;the cyber exposure management &amp;amp; security company&lt;/strong&gt;, protects the entire attack surface and manages an organization’s cyber risk exposure in real time.&amp;nbsp;In a rapidly evolving, perimeter-less world, Armis ensures that organizations&amp;nbsp;continuously &lt;strong&gt;see&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;protect&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;manage&lt;/strong&gt; all critical assets - from the&lt;strong&gt; ground to&amp;nbsp;the cloud&lt;/strong&gt;. Armis secures Fortune 100, 200 and 500 companies as well as&amp;nbsp;national governments, state and local entities to help keep critical&amp;nbsp;infrastructure, economies and society stay safe and secure 24/7.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Armis is a&amp;nbsp;privately held company headquartered in California.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Network research is at the core of how Armis works. As an agentless platform, everything we know about a device starts with the network - and this team owns that layer end to end.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll work across the full spectrum: IT, OT, IoT, medical, industrial. Researching protocols, dissecting traffic, and turning raw network data into accurate device insights at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the deep packet inspection pipeline from initial protocol research through to production code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research network protocols and device behaviors - inspecting traffic, modeling architectures, and building the understanding that drives accurate client insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop core platform features based on network activity, from protocol parsers to device classification logic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dig into the security posture of devices and protocols at the network layer - identifying implementation flaws, documenting findings, and driving responsible disclosure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Product, Data, and other R&amp;amp;D teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Join customer POCs when it matters - debugging hard problems in time-sensitive environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in network research and traffic inspection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of Python development on production systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of network concepts, protocols, and infrastructures - across IT and ideally OT/ICS or medical environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SQL and database fundamentals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong sense of ownership and the ability to operate on a tight schedule without losing rigor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in cybersecurity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building features for large-scale distributed systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reverse engineering experience - binary analysis, protocol RE, Wireshark/Scapy-level dissection of undocumented protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with threat and malware analysis - understanding attacker behavior at the network layer.&lt;/li&gt;
